cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with text-to-speech conversion using neural networks. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper involves generating speech from text using a WaveNet vocoder. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a fully parallel neural text-to-speech system. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper involves training neural networks for speech synthesis. 
- cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) is a possible category as the paper deals with converting text to spectrogram, which is a type of signal processing.
